 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-W2-008: Close guidance feedback loop with drift detection and GoalDrift signal emission. PROBLEM: guidance.rs build_footer() computes M(t) and emits a footer, but there is no DETECT_DRIFT transition monitoring access logs for transact gaps or tool absence. INV-GUIDANCE-004 requires drift signal emission when transact_gap > 5 bash commands. M(t) sub-metrics are computed but not fed back into threshold adjustment or guidance evolution. No GoalDrift signals emitted. The EVOLVE transition (pruning ineffective guidance) does not exist. Guidance is a display mechanism, not a convergence mechanism. SOLUTION: (1) Implement detect_drift(store, current_tx, now) that checks: time since last braid observe/transact vs time since last bash command. If gap exceeds threshold, emit GoalDrift signal. (2) Store GoalDrift as datoms (:signal/type :goal-drift, :signal/severity N, :signal/transact-gap N). (3) Wire drift severity into guidance footer urgency: low drift → suggestion, medium → recommendation, high → imperative. (4) Track guidance effectiveness: when agent follows a suggestion and F(S) improves, increment the suggestion's effectiveness score. When F(S) degrades after following guidance, decrement. This closes the loop. VERIFICATION: (1) Unit test: 10 consecutive non-transact commands → GoalDrift signal emitted. (2) Unit test: interleaved observe/bash commands → no GoalDrift. (3) E2E: guidance urgency escalates as drift increases. DEPENDS-ON: W0-004 (GoalDrift signal definition). INTERACTS-WITH: W0-002 (now injection needed for time comparison), ARCH-007 (signal datoms consumed)."
